18:32.752 --> 18:33.719
Hey.

18:33.753 --> 18:35.587
Can I buy you a beer?

18:37.523 --> 18:38.790
You wanna talk about what just happened?

18:40.526 --> 18:43.295
You mean how the director
had a nervous breakdown?

18:43.329 --> 18:44.696
I'm talking about you and Danny.

18:44.731 --> 18:47.666
- (Clears throat)
- Something I seem to do a lot of lately.

18:49.202 --> 18:52.204
We rehearsed that scene a million times.

18:52.238 --> 18:54.473
He got confused. It could happen to anybody.

18:54.507 --> 18:56.008
Could it?

18:57.243 --> 19:00.145
I just can't help feeling that
you two have something more,

19:00.179 --> 19:01.980
and I don't even think that you realize it.

19:02.982 --> 19:05.217
- Ben, he's my...
- Your best friend. Yeah, I know.

19:05.251 --> 19:07.753
You say that more often than you say
"boyfriend."

19:07.787 --> 19:10.122
- Well, it's true, he is!
- Oh, come on, Riley!

19:10.156 --> 19:12.090
You have to see it!

19:13.126 --> 19:14.927
That moment on the roof?

19:14.961 --> 19:17.629
The love note?
You hiding him and lying to me?

19:18.831 --> 19:20.666
I can't do this.

19:20.700 --> 19:23.602
I can't be in a relationship where
I'm constantly questioning everything.

19:24.637 --> 19:26.471
I always feel like I'm in second place.

19:28.441 --> 19:29.408
Wait.

19:30.476 --> 19:31.677
Are you breaking up with me?

19:32.745 --> 19:35.547
Because that's not fair.
I didn't do anything wrong.

19:35.581 --> 19:37.316
Can you look me in the eyes right now

19:37.350 --> 19:39.251
and tell me that you don't
have feelings for Danny?

19:39.285 --> 19:42.454
But I spent my whole life
being in love with you.

19:42.488 --> 19:46.358
I never even had a minute to think
about how I feel about Danny.

19:46.392 --> 19:47.526
(Voice breaking) Well,
maybe it's time you did.

19:50.563 --> 19:52.431
And maybe we take a time out while you do.

19:53.499 --> 19:55.367
- Ben.
- I'm sorry, Riley.

19:58.338 --> 19:59.338
I just...

20:00.373 --> 20:01.473
I don't know what else to do.

20:02.575 --> 20:03.675
I love you, but...

20:04.711 --> 20:06.411
Something just doesn't feel right.

20:15.488 --> 20:17.356
(Crying)

20:23.292 --> 20:26.094
- What do you want?
- Hello, roomie.

20:26.128 --> 20:27.762
You're not coming in here.

20:27.797 --> 20:29.097
Absolutely nothing in that lease

20:29.131 --> 20:31.066
says that I won't be living here with you.

20:32.134 --> 20:33.902
Joshua: This isn't gonna get rid of me.

20:33.936 --> 20:36.204
Bonnie: Well, take a look at these.

20:36.238 --> 20:38.039
Joshua: I've seen those.

20:38.074 --> 20:39.808
Bonnie: How about one of these?

20:39.842 --> 20:40.976
Joshua: Oh my God.

20:41.010 --> 20:43.244
- I'm out of here.
- Same way I got rid

20:43.279 --> 20:46.014
of my ex-husband! Buh-bye!

